Package com.pb.sawdust.util.collections

Provides classes extending the standard Java collections api.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    InjectiveMap<K,V>
    An InjectiveMap is a map whose keys map to unique values.
    SetDeque<E>
    A SetDeque is a deque which can contain no repeated values.
    SetList<E>
    A SetList is a list which can contain no repeated values.
    SetQueue<E>
    A SetQueue is a queue which can contain no repeated values.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractSetDeque<E>
    The AbstractSetDeque class provides a basic implementation of the SetDeque interface to lower the burden for programmers.
    AbstractSetList<E>
    The AbstractSetList class provides a basic implementation of the SetList interface to lower the burden for programmers.
    AbstractSetQueue<E>
    The AbstractSetQueue class provides a basic implementation of the SetQueue interface to lower the burden for programmers.
    ArraySetList<E>
    The ArraySetList is a AbstractSetList which uses an java.util.ArrayList as its backing list.
    CollectionOrder
    The CollectionOrder class provides methods for determining the sorting order of a collection.
    GenericInjectiveMap<K,V>
    The GenericInjectiveMap provides a basic implementation of an injective map.
    IndexedElement<E>
    The IndexedElement class is used to wrap an object with an integer index.
    InjectiveBiEnumMap<K extends java.lang.Enum<K>,V extends java.lang.Enum<V>>
    The InjectiveBiEnumMap class is an injective map in which both keys and values are constants from enums.
    InjectiveEnumHashMap<K extends java.lang.Enum<K>,V>
    The InjectiveEnumHashMap is an injective map whose key values are constants from a specific enum instance and whose value-to-key mapping is maintained in a hash map.
    InjectiveEnumMap<K extends java.lang.Enum<K>,V>
    The InjectiveEnumMap is an injective map whose key values are constants from a specific enum instance.
    InjectiveHashMap<K,V>
    The InjectiveHashMap is an injective map whose mappings are maintained in hash maps.
    LinkedSetList<E>
    The LinkedSetList is a AbstractSetList which uses an java.util.LinkedList as its backing list.
    OrderEnforcingQueue<E>
    The OrderEnforcingQueue provides a BlockingQueue whose indexed elements will always be returned in consecutive order.
    UnmodifiableCollections
    The UnmodifiableCollections provides unmodifiable versions of collection classes.
